# TODO - Active Roadmap

## Execution Policy
1. This file tracks only active and upcoming work.
2. Completed work is tracked in DONE.

## Goal: real-world readiness 9.5/10
Current: ~9/10 — as of 2026-07-13 the engineering-completable backlog is closed
and then hardened. Earlier: D5 (keychain default + Homebrew/Windows scaffolding),
AR11, G13, QA-2 and the DX items (DX17 core, DX18 repair, DX19, DX24). The
2026-07-13 wave (see "HARDENING WAVE" below) added the `completion` command
(23 CLI commands), a machine-checked MCP `outputSchema`/`structuredContent`
contract, MCP stdio stdout-purity guarantees, and raised the MCP coverage gate to
90/80. `npm run check` is green, all governance gates pass, and prod `npm audit`
is clean. What remains is NOT engineering-completable offline: AR9 (deferred by
decision), CR22 + DX17 pipeline wiring + Homebrew/Windows real verification (need
a live instance / first publish / Windows host), and the BA1–8 owner/business
decisions (incl. npm publish, which is owner-gated).

