## TRIPLE GAP ANALYSIS (2026-06-12) — Senior Dev / Architect / QA
Third review pass: what is MISSING (gaps, not bugs). Numbered G*.
Does not repeat AR/CR/DX. The same-day best-practice fixes (0 audit
vulnerabilities, core lint gate, package metadata, CONTRIBUTING.md) are in DONE.

### Senior Dev — missing capabilities in the code
- [x] **G1. OAuth 2.0 auth** — DONE 2026-06-16 (CLI + MCP; additive, Basic default):
      SN_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID + SN_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET (CLI also _<PROFILE>) → OAuth 2.0
      password grant at oauth_token.do → Bearer + refresh on expiry/401. The token
      manager lives in @syncrona/sn-transport (shared, IO-free; ARCH-001); the CLI
      (snClient axios interceptors) and the MCP server (servicenowCore fetch) both
      use it. Tests: oauth.test.ts (4) + e2e Bearer-on-wire + mcp oauth.test.js (3).
      Legacy sys.scripts.do fallback stays Basic (best-effort; CR22). Full
      authorization-code / SSO grant is future.
- [x] **G2. Schema validation for sync.config.js** — DONE 2026-06-12:
      validateConfigShape in config.ts (no new dependency) — wrong type = hard
      error, unknown key = warning listing the valid options; 4 new tests
      (configValidation.test.ts).
- [x] **G3. Download progress/resume** — DONE 2026-06-21: `downloadAllFiles`
      now pulls one table at a time, logging per-table progress ([i/N]) and
      recording each completed table in `sync.download.checkpoint.json`
      (downloadCheckpoint.ts) so an interrupted pull resumes instead of starting
      over; the checkpoint is cleared on full success and ignored when stale
      (different scope). The bulk endpoint is now called per table (falling back
      to the Table API once the scoped endpoint is unavailable). Resume/progress
      logic is an injected-deps orchestration (downloadTablesWithResume) — 8
      tests (downloadResume + downloadCheckpoint). Trade-off: more requests on
      the scoped-app path in exchange for resumability + visible progress.
- [x] **G4. Rate-limit awareness in the MCP client** — DONE 2026-06-12: shared
      MAX_REQUESTS_PER_SECOND=20 constant in sn-transport; the mcp client spaces
      requests (acquireRequestSlot, min 50ms interval) instead of relying only on
      429 retries.
- [x] **G5. Typed CLI args** — DONE 2026-06-12: typedHandler<TArgs> helper in
      cliCommands.ts — handler bodies are type-checked against TArgs; the 16
      scattered `as unknown as` casts were replaced with one controlled bridge.
      (Full InferredOptionTypes derivation from the options declarations remains a
      possible follow-up.)

### Architect — missing infrastructure
- [x] **G6. Release automation** — DONE 2026-06-21: Changesets wired in
      (.changeset/, npm run changeset / version-packages / release); @syncrona/*
      version in lockstep. Publishing stays owner-gated (npm scope + 2FA). See DONE.
- [~] **G7. CLI diagnostics telemetry** — PARTIAL 2026-06-13: opt-in local
      diagnostic log shipped — SYNCRONA_DIAGNOSTIC_LOG=1 appends CLI output to
      ~/.syncrona/logs/cli.log (rotation, off by default, documented in
      SECURITY.md). isDiagnosticLogEnabled + 3 tests. Remaining: structured
      metrics/telemetry for the KPI set (BA7) — needs an opt-in events schema.
- [x] **G8. Plugin API contract** — DONE 2026-06-13: pluginContract.test.ts pins
      the public plugin contract on two layers — (1) a `referencePlugin` typed
      against `Sync.Plugin`/`PluginFunc`/`FileContext` so an incompatible
      interface change fails to COMPILE, and (2) a conforming plugin loaded
      through the real PluginManager from <rootDir>/node_modules/<name>,
      asserting call shape, output chaining, first-match rule selection, and
      short-circuit on success:false. 4 tests. Related to DX13.
- [x] **G9. Proxy/TLS configuration** — DONE 2026-06-21: the CLI honors
      HTTPS_PROXY/HTTP_PROXY/NO_PROXY automatically (axios Node adapter); custom
      CA bundles via SYNCRONA_CA_BUNDLE (+ Node's NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS, which also
      covers the MCP fetch client) and an explicit, warned
      SYNCRONA_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0 opt-out, applied through a shared
      https.Agent on every request incl. the OAuth token endpoint. Policy is a
      pure helper in sn-transport (resolveTlsPolicy); 17 tests (tlsPolicy.test.ts).
      Documented in README. Residual: HTTPS_PROXY for the MCP native-fetch client
