      NOT claim missing config.
- [x] **QA-8. Default-profile store fallback untested in both resolveConfig
      variants** — DONE 2026-07-01: resolveConfig.ts async (line 82) and sync
      (line 99) fallbacks to the `"default"` stored profile — the primary
      "jira-login, then just use it" path — were uncovered, as was the
      configFromStored partial-record guard (line 59). Added three tests in
      jira.test.ts: async + sync no-profile/no-env resolution via a mocked
      store (asserting the store is asked for "default"), and a stored record
      with a missing token resolving to null instead of a broken config.
- [x] **QA-9. ARCH-10's caret escaping not pinned at the call sites** — DONE
      2026-07-01: snClientMethods.test.ts exercised getScopeId/getUserSysId
      only with benign values (`x_acme_app`, `admin`), and index.test.js
      exercised buildRecentChangesQuery only with a benign scope — removing
      `escapeQueryValue` from any interpolation site would have passed the
      suite. Added caret-bearing assertions at both core sites
      (`x_acme_app^sys_id=ADMIN` → `scope=x_acme_app sys_id=ADMIN`) and the
      recent-changes query builder.
- [x] **QA-10. jiraUndecryptableMessage contract asserted only through
      mocks** — DONE 2026-07-01: messages.ts functions coverage was 0% — the
