      examples for dev/push/download/build/status/login/use/mcp, incl.
      `push --dry-run`, `push --diff main`, `push --ci`. Also set
      `.scriptName("syncrona")` so help shows `syncrona <cmd>` not `index.js`.
      e2e smoke test asserts `push --help` carries the examples.

**DX6: The `--diff` flag is unclear**
- CORRECTION 2026-06-13: the premise was wrong. `push --diff <branch>` already
  pushes ONLY the changed files (gitDiffToEncodedPaths → `git diff <branch>...`
  → getAppFileList over just those paths). It is already a changed-only push, so
  a separate `--changed-only` flag would just duplicate `--diff`. The real gap
  was clarity: `push --diff` = filter to changed files; `build --diff` = build
  all but write sync.diff.manifest.json for deploy.
- [x] ~~Add a --changed-only flag~~ — not needed (push --diff is the changed-only
  push). RESOLVED as a docs fix.
- [x] Document the two meanings — DONE 2026-06-13: README "Using the diff option"
  rewritten to contrast push vs build; --diff option describe and the push --diff
  help example corrected (the example previously mislabeled it as audit-only).

**DX7: `--instance-profile` on EVERY command is verbose**
- Typical work: `syncrona status --instance-profile dev`,
  `syncrona push --instance-profile dev`.
- The user has to remember the flag every time.
- [x] Add a `.syncrona-local` config — DONE 2026-06-13: a gitignored
      `.syncrona-local` (`{ "instanceProfile": "dev" }`) in the working dir sets a
      default profile; explicit --instance-profile still wins. resolveInstanceProfile
      in commandHelpers; 4 tests; documented in MULTI_INSTANCE.md; added to .gitignore.
- [x] Persist profile in `syncrona use` — N/A 2026-06-13: `use` selects the
      active *stored instance* (store-based); `.syncrona-local` sets the env-var
      *profile* default (DX7, done). Different mechanisms — not merged by design.

