      lands; KPI set defined in §7.
- [~] **BA8. Provenance / IP (Risk R1)** — LICENSING FIX APPLIED 2026-06-21.
      Deep BA found the real conflict: upstream Sincronia is **GPL-3.0**
      (LICENSE file + @sincronia/core package.json) but this fork was relicensed
      to **MIT** with no attribution — a GPL violation that blocked any
      distribution. Fixed: LICENSE replaced with verbatim GPL-3.0, all 14
      package.json `license` fields → `GPL-3.0-or-later`, added `NOTICE`
      (copyright + Sincronia/Nuvolo attribution + trademark notice), README
      license section rewritten. Gate green. REMAINING [owner/legal]: a lawyer's
      sign-off on the GPL-3.0-only vs -or-later variant and that no
      employer-proprietary code is mixed in, BEFORE the first public publish.
      Note: GPL copyleft forecloses a closed-source/proprietary paid tier
      (see deep BA §1/§3 — OSS or SaaS/support monetization only).
